THE UMBU.

So wide are the boughs and trunk of this tree, that the sun never sees its soot. It affords plenty of shade to fifty persons seated beneath it, and completely defends them against the rain. The linden trees of Europe are mere ⁴dwarfs compared with an aged umbu.
